EXPLANATION – Matter in bolded italics is new; matter between brackets [omitted material] is material to be omitted.
AN ACT relating to housing; requiring the Housing Division of the Department of
Business and Industry to establish a pilot program to buy down the
interest rate on mortgage loans for certain eligible borrowers; making
an appropriation for the pilot program; and providing other matters
properly relating thereto.
Legislative Counsel’s Digest:
1 Existing law authorizes the Housing Division of the Department of Business and Industry
2 to enter into instruments, agreements and other transactions for certain purposes, including:
3 (1) reducing or modifying the amount or duration of any payment, interest rate, spread or
4 similar risk; and (2) lowering the cost of borrowing when used in combination with the
5 issuance or carrying of bonds or investments. (NRS 319.167) Section 1 of this bill requires
6 the Division to establish a pilot program for certain eligible borrowers to buy down the
7 interest rate of a 30-year fixed-rate mortgage loan for an owner-occupied residence for such
8 an eligible borrower in this State. Section 1 requires the eligible borrower to: (1) be in the
9 process of obtaining his or her first mortgage loan on a residence for the eligible borrower; (2)
10 qualify as a first-time homebuyer; (3) with certain exceptions, have a household income of not
11 more than 160 percent of the median income for the county in this State in which the
12 residence is located; and (4) meet certain underwriting criteria. Section 1 further authorizes
13 the Division to establish a process for an eligible borrower to obtain a waiver of the household
14 income requirement.
15 Section 2 of this bill makes an appropriation to the Division for the purpose of
16 establishing and carrying out the pilot program.

