THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF NEVADA, REPRESENTED IN
SENATE AND ASSEMBLY, DO ENACT AS FOLLOWS:
1 Section 1. Chapter 319 of NRS is hereby amended by adding thereto a new
2 section to read as follows:
3 1. The Division shall, subject to the availability of funds appropriated for
4 such a purpose, establish a pilot program for an eligible borrower who meets the
5 qualifications set forth in subsection 3 to buy down the interest rate of a fixed-
6 rate mortgage loan with an amortization period of 30 years for an owner-
7 occupied residence in this State for the eligible borrower that is obtained from a
8 lending institution approved by the Division in accordance with any regulations
9 adopted pursuant to subsection 5.
10 2. The pilot program established pursuant to subsection 1 must, without
11 limitation:
12 (a) Include a process for an eligible borrower to apply to participate in the
13 program; and
14 (b) Provide for a buy down for the mortgage loan of the eligible borrower.
15 3. Except as otherwise provided in subsection 4, an eligible borrower may
16 receive assistance from the pilot program established pursuant to subsection 1 if
17 the eligible borrower:
18 (a) Is in the process of obtaining his or her first mortgage loan from a
19 lending institution approved by the Division for the purchase of an owner-
20 occupied residence.
21 (b) Qualifies as a first-time homebuyer. An eligible borrower qualifies as a
22 first-time homebuyer if:
23 (1) The eligible borrower and, except as otherwise provided in
24 subparagraphs (2) and (3), the spouse of the eligible borrower, if applicable, have
25 had no ownership interest in any residential real property at any time during the
26 3-year period immediately preceding the date on which a mortgage for the
27 residence is or will be executed;
28 (2) The eligible borrower is a single person who is a displaced
29 homemaker and, except for owning a home with his or her spouse or residing in
30 a home owned by his or her spouse, meets the requirements of subparagraph (1);
31 or
32 (3) The eligible borrower is a single person who is a single parent and
33 who, except for owning a home with his or her spouse or residing in a home
34 owned by his or her spouse while married, meets the requirements of
35 subparagraph (1).
36 (c) Has a household income of not more than 160 percent of the median
37 income for the county in this State in which the residence to be purchased is
38 located.
39 (d) Meets any criteria for underwriting established by the lending institution.
40 (e) Meets any other requirement prescribed by the Division by regulation.
41 4. The Division may establish a process for an eligible borrower who does
42 not meet the household income requirement set forth in paragraph (c) of
43 subsection 3 to apply to the Division for a waiver of that requirement.
44 5. The Division may adopt regulations to carry out the provisions of this
45 section, which may include, without limitation:
46 (a) The requirements for a lending institution to be approved to participate in
47 the program; and
48 (b) The procedures to apply for a waiver from the Division pursuant to
49 subsection 4.

